ere outdated by the time it was released and that the gameplay wasn't as compelling as it seemed when i first played the supremely addictive Diablo1.  Possibly because beta forced me to play as a barbarian, ugh...  After rebalancing, i think most people were content with the game's balance.  You also have to consider the entire Blizzard line when thinking about this.  Diablo 1, the Warcraft series, Starcraft which was possibly the best balanced game i've ever played.  Their overall catalog is full of fun, well balanced games, and bugs were dealt with quickly.  Blizzard ain't perfect, but compared to the half-assed methods SOE utilizes...  i expect good things. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kildaretest>Kildaretest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 9:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fires of heaven website</span><hr size=1> Based on what Furor said... I would be happy just riding Griffons.... that sounds Very cool. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=savannaskyphire>Savanna Skyphire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 10:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fires of heaven website</span><hr size=1> Hear nothing but good about this game and I too drool everytime I read something. This last week I have not wanted to even be part of EQ just because you can only (imo) screw people over for so long with unfinished, untested zones and encounters.  WoW may be taking their sweet time but they r doing it how it should be done.  They don't want to release a product that isn't ready.  What's scary is that everyone that has seen it says how it's seems ready to ship already.  <br>
<br>
In our guild we have a few blizzard peeps as most know, Tigole being the one most well known (even tho some of the people that have been with the company longer like Thatia/Thorax, who was originally a wiz on EQ btw and is an artist for them, are less well known).  Where have they been for the last 6months to year?  Definitely not playing EQ and everytime they do log in to say hi or whatever they say how they can't imagine playing EQ and how unbelieveable WoW is compared to it.  <br>
<br>
To me that is what is going to make WoW good...they have people that, like Furor mentioned have played through the timesinks, the broken encounters etc.  They have experienced the frustrations we all have and are designing a game that is addressing those. I have a lot of faith in these people that some of us have had the pleasure of playing beside.  I couldn't be more excited to play this game.  <br>
<br>
