<br>
But...<br>
<br>
It's very easy to villify what you have in your hand (EQ, DAoC, AO, SB, NWN, whatever) and heap praises on what yet doesn't really exist yet.<br>
<br>
And as we all know, an MMORPG is not just the pretty client software or the server backend or the lore or the quest system or the character system or the customer service or the community. It's all the stuff meshed together. I think WoW has the best shot among all the upcoming titles to be the best and to be the best for a very long time. I hope they are...because I quite frankly love the somewhat cartoony style. I dig the gnomes building quirky inventions and the big nasty green orcs.<br>
<br>
